init_text: You're Barack Obama. 4 years into your retirement, you awake to find a letter with no return address on your bedside table. It reads "I hope you've had a chance to relax Barack...but pack your bags and call the number below. It's time to start the real job." Signed simply, "JFK."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: you remember her doing something like this before, and you smile and shake your head.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: she's a Harvard Law student now.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You chuckle to yourself and think about how she's going to be a great lawyer.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You dial the number on the note and hear a familiar voice on the other end.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You've met him before, and he's a great kid.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He's a little older than Malia, but you're glad that she's found someone to be with.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He's a kind, hardworking young man who's going to be a doctor.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You're sure that Malia will be a great lawyer, but Matt will be a great doctor.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He's already got the bedside manner for it.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You ask what the occasion is and Matt says that he can't tell you.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You tell her that she should wear her best dress and that you will wear your best suit.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You're surprised to see that Malia is pregnant.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You ask her how long she's been pregnant and she says that she's been pregnant for about a month.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She says that she's been keeping it a secret from you and that she was planning on telling you tonight.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You're surprised to hear that you're going to be a grandparent, but you're happy.
